v0.7.2: parallel cdb, xunit v3, CI restructure

- Parallel cdb: pre-warm + size-weighted semaphore, ~3x faster on real batches.
- xunit v2 -> v3 (xunit.v3 3.2.2); 57 sites adopted TestContext.Current.CancellationToken.
- CI restructure: test/build/release split, build tag-only, HISTORY tag-match verify, awk release-notes extraction.
- GH Actions SHA pins bumped; cleared Node 20 deprecation.
- About box dep tagline now derived from @(PackageReference); Microsoft.*/System.* filtered.
- UI log: [mm:ss] stamps, "Analysis complete in Xm Ys", periodic cdb progress, blank-line normalization.
- EventLogParser.ParseNvlddmkmEventXml + fixture machinery for classifier drift.
- setupapi.dev.log fixture corpus + extractor with unit tests.
- Docs sweep: ARCHITECTURE/README/CONTRIBUTING refreshed.

----

v0.7.1: LiveKernel dumps, Markdown reports, since-date, MinVer

- LiveKernel watchdog dumps: scans C:\Windows\LiveKernelReports for
  non-BSOD kernel dumps (0x117 / 0x141 / 0x1B0 / 0x1B8). Elevated copy
  reads system minidumps and LiveKernel dumps in one UAC round-trip.
  BugcheckCatalog gains 0x113, 0x141, 0x1B0, 0x1B8 with live-dump flag.
  Max LiveKernel input clamped to [1, 1000]; effective cap surfaces in
  SCOPE.
- Reports are Markdown: report.md + paired report_dumps.md with full
  cdb stack traces. TOC, ## headers, tables, fenced code. Frequency
  chart buckets by ISO 8601 weeks (Monday start) and labels rows with
  ISO year-week.
- Since-date input: bidirectionally bound to Max Days, persisted in
  AppSettings. All MaxDays cutoffs anchored at midnight.
- Orphan cdb cache surfacing: cached transcripts for rotated-out
  LiveKernel dumps now picked up. Both scan cap and orphan cap surface
  in SCOPE via CollectionTruncation flags.
- Helper hardening: reparse-point defense extends to per-run and
  per-dump subdirectories. LiveKernel copy runs independently of
  minidump dir existence.
- Fixture corpus: redacted real-world cdb transcripts (0x113, 0x116,
  0x133, 0x141, 0x1B8) with expected ExtractCdbSummary output.
- CdbLocator prefers cdbx64.exe in the WindowsApps fallback scan.
- MinVer: version derived from the most recent v* tag. Release builds
  read clean; per-commit artifacts read [SNAPSHOT] with commit-height
  suffix.

